name: Arash Saidi
tweet: @PWengerden There are no typos, and Chat-GPT doesn't have a layer that autocorrects. Typos are considered just the same as other words (as far as I know). With enough training data you get enough typos to train on!

name: Arash Saidi
tweet: This is why you can "trick" it to provide so many amusing and wrong answers. Everything Chat-GPT does is an approximation of whatever it has learned from. It looks like it is reasoning, but it is just trying to get as close to its data as possible.

name: Arash Saidi
tweet: In the case below the sentence does not make sense, so why does Chat-GPT respond? Well, it is a statistical model. "Write a letter" and "write a door" are somehow statistically similar, so is "baking in the oven" and "baking in the dove".  https://t.co/MrA9m4hszI

name: Arash Saidi
tweet: Chat-GPT is a zero/one/few shot model. This means that it can provide an answer based on zero, one or a few examples. This is where it shines, and what makes it so impressive.

name: Arash Saidi
tweet: Chat-GPT is a large language model based on the transformer deep learning architecture. It is a generative model, so the answers are created rather than picked from a group of pre-defined answers.

name: Arash Saidi
tweet: It's quite easy to trick Chat-GPT to give you answers to questions that don't make sense. Why? üßµ
